Subject: Re: [T2] Mountain passes in NC vs Sierra Nevada...



> ...or my regular route for backbacking: leave Visalia, CA (300'), arrive at
> Mineral King Valley roads end, (7800') after about 4 hours on the road.
> Ahhh, the Sierra Nevada...

Yes, not that you mention it on my mini-road-trip this summer we went from the railroad museum in Sacramento (elevation 30) to Echo 
Summit (7382) in about 2 hours and 90 miles.  The elevation change is gradual on US50, though, so it didn't seem like all that much of a 
climb.  The drop down into the Tahoe basin was much quicker, as was the drop from Tahoe to Carson City.

George

