> > >
> > > I thought Saluda grade was bad on I-26 ( about a 3 mile 6 % grade) but
> Old
> > > Fort puts it to shame!!!
> >
> > We've got to get you out to the Left Coast where you can climb some real
> mountains!  How about US 395 between Bishop and Carson
> > City in the Sierras?  Start at Bishop, elevation 4100 feet.  In the next
> 15 miles, climb to Sherwin Summit (7000).  About 30 miles later you
> > get to Deadman Summit (8041).  30 more miles gets you to Conway Summit
> (8138) and another 20 to Devil's Gate Summit (7519).  From
> > there you drop into Gardnerville at 4700 feet.  Typically, my stock 1600DP
> bus (low compression Mexican engine) will maintain 30-35MPH
> > on the 6%+ grades on this route.  With the thin air, I doubt that it's
> making much more than 30HP.  The scenery is so pretty that the slow
> > speeds aren't a bother.
> >
> > Another route for hill-climbers is from Badwater (280 feet _below_ sea
> level) to Emigrant Pass (5318 feet) in Death Valley.  This route is
> > about 50 miles and the temperatures can be a tad warm.
> >
> > I still think that the worst climb I've done is the western approach to
> Jerome.  That road is literally carved out of a cliff.
